# Response Code Formatting

## Shell commands — plain blocks only

Never add line numbers or vertical bar prefixes to shell command blocks.

```bash
# CORRECT — user can copy-paste directly
cd /path/to/project
npm install
npm run dev
```

```
# WRONG — line numbers break copy-paste
1 | cd /path/to/project
2 | npm install
3 | npm run dev
```

## Existing codebase references

When citing code **already in the codebase**, use the `startLine:endLine:filepath` format so Cursor renders a navigable link:

```12:18:src/components/screens/AvatarSpeechScreen.tsx
// code snippet here
```

## New or proposed code

Use a plain fenced block with just the language tag — no line numbers, no file path in the fence:

```typescript
export function myNewFunction() { ... }
```
